---
---
<section class="page-container section-spacer" data-orb="3">
  <div class="geo-divider">
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-blue);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-coral);"></span>
    <span class="geo-circle" style="background: var(--color-geo-teal);"></span>
  </div>
  <p class="eyebrow fade-in">philosophy</p>
  <h2 class="fade-in-up delay-1" style="max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);">Built for ADHD brains, not against them.</h2>
  <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);">
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-2">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">01</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Forgiving streaks</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">A missed day never resets progress to zero. Streaks degrade gently, one miss barely dents your momentum.</p>
      <p class="body-small">Habit science shows consistency matters more than perfection. elly is built on that idea.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-3">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">02</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Tiny first steps</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Vague tasks become concrete 2-5 minute actions. Not "Run 5k" but "Put on running shoes."</p>
      <p class="body-small">AI breaks down what you're avoiding into the smallest version that still counts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-4">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">03</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Time you can see</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">"This afternoon" becomes "3:00-3:30 PM Walk." Visual timelines replace vague reminders.</p>
      <p class="body-small">Time blindness is real. elly makes time visible through color-coded blocks and scheduled events.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-5">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">04</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">No judgment</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Options offered, never shoulds. No guilt-toned copy. No streak-breaking shame.</p>
      <p class="body-small">The app suggests, you choose. Your data, your pace.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-6">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">05</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Insights, not scores</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Correlations, mood trends, habit heatmaps, described like a friend noticing things, not a performance review.</p>
      <p class="body-small">LLM narrates patterns from your data in neutral, helpful language.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="fade-in-up delay-7">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-geo-coral); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block;">06</span>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your data. Full stop.</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">SQLite on your disk. Encrypted fields. Only network calls: your LLM API and optional Telegram bot.</p>
      <p class="body-small">No telemetry. No analytics. No cloud sync. The backend is public and auditable. <a href="https://github.com/Kxetch/elly-server" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the source</a> instead of taking it on trust.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
